           CLARIFICATION FOR THE ACCOUNTING SYSTEMS DOCUMENTATION
           ------------------------------------------------------
           ------------------------------------------------------


Written by : Shirley Chiang, Mgr., HQ Applications Support Unit
      Date :  January 03, 1986




      Recently I received an RFI from the field concerning the ACOUNT.DOC, a 
   reference manual describing our network's accounting system, which has been 
   updated as of Nov. 15, '85.  A few questions have arisen since within the
   preface of this document the ACCT2.DOC and Account-II system are referenced
   but with no clear indication explaining what they are.  Therefore I would
   like to share with you some of my knowledge about the legitimacy of these 
   documents and the status of the Account-II system project.


   (1)  About the ACCT2.DOC
    
         - Account-II system is a future system to replace the current
           Account-I system

         - The preliminary system specification is documented in the 
           ACCT2.DOC

         - The actual code implementation has yet to be started since
           considerable amount of changes for various s/w disciplines
           is anticipated within the network, such as RAM, ISIS, Node
           Code and other billing processes, etc.  It is expected the
           transition from the old system to the new one be as trans-
           parent as possible and the customers will be informed ahead
           of the time when such event occurs and be given detailed ins-
           tructions on systems deployment.

         - The major features of Account-II are:

                     0  multiple precision accounting message formats,
                     0  16 bits for host number,
                     0  48 bits for invoice/session number, etc.

         - Conservatively speaking, Account-II will not be in place in the
           public network until late this year or early '87.

         - The private networks will have to be upgraded to conform with
           the new system eventually.

   (2)  About the ACOUNT.DOC

         - The Nov. '84 version is still the great BIBLE.  The Nov. '85
           version was released a little too early for the actual functional
           design of the Consat/Outdial has just been completed.

         - The additional features in the Nov. '85 version primarily document
           the accounting behavior of the upcoming Consat/Outdial service
           which is currrently under development and won't be ready for beta-
           test until May.  In another words, the Nov. '85 document should not
           be accounted as a true reference manual until the Outdial s/w is 
           matured to complement the accounting system.

         - Basically the Outdial will utilize the existing ISIS B7 message to
           report the accounting addendum (to ISIS) for its sessions. (ISIS
           and Node Code will then send the information to the Sup through
           accounting message 14 over command circuit.)

         - I had requested the author of the document to comment properly
           in the Preface where ACOUNT.DOC is mentioned.  it should be worded
           as follows:

           "ACOUNT.DOC This document describes Tymnet accounting and will be
                       superceded by the ACCT2.DOC in the future when the
                       Account-II system is implemented."



