                      SNA INTERFACE MEMORY REQUIREMENTS
                      ---------------------------------
                      ---------------------------------


Written by : David Pau, HQ Network Staff Consultant
      Date : January 15, 1986




      The following table indicates the memory requirements of an SNA 
   interface running either version 1.03 or 1.04 with different device
   configurations:


       TOTAL NO. OF DEVICES      
       (Any Combination of                  MEMORY REQUIRED    
       Printers and CRTs)                      (k-BYTE)
       ====================                 ===============

               16                              228
	
               32                              328         

               48                              441

               64                              524

               80                              620

               96                              708                      

      
      General Guidelines:

        - Printer and CRT require the same amount of memory.

        - Although only 1.04 provides printer support, memory requirements
          for both 1.03 and 1.04 are very close.

        - The overhead of an SNA interface is about 135 K-byte and each
          device needs about 6 to 6.2 K-byte of memory.
      
        - At this point in time, no more than 96 devices are recommanded
          on each SNA interface.


      We will keep you all informed when further information on this subject
   is available.



