:                 |                   :                -----                 :
:              -------                :                 _|_                  :
:            COMPILATION              :                 \ /                  :
:              -------                :          ________'________           :
:                _|_                  :         |       NEM       |          :
:  _________     \ /       ________   :         |  SLOT NIB FILE  |          :
: | TMCS    |  ___`____   |        |  :         |_________________|          :
: | SLOT    | | OBJECT |  | PATCH  |  :                  |                   :
: | TYMFILE | |  CODE  |  | FILE   |  :..................|...................:
: |_________| |________|  |________|  :                  |                  
:     |           |           |       :             -----------             
:     |           |           |       :           LOADII  OR  ELF           
:     |         -----         |       :             -----------             
:     |____|   RUN NAD   |____|       :                 _|_
:               -----                 :                 \ /
:                _|_                  :          ________'________
:                \ /                  :         |     RUNNING     |
:         ________'________           :         |    NEM  SLOT    |
:        |      TMCS       |          :         |_________________|
:        |  SLOT NIB FILE  |          :                  |
:        |_________________|          :                  |
:                 |                   :                  |
:.................|...................:                  |
                  |                                      |
              ---------                                  |
            LOADII OR ELF                                |
              ---------                                  |
                 _|_                                     |
                 \ /                                     |
          ________'________                              |
         |                 |  /|                         |
         |     RUNNING     | / ========================= |
         |    TMCS SLOT    | \ ==========================|
         |_________________|  \|

   Once  the  software  is installed it is necessary to define  the network
   configuration  to  TMCS.   Network  configuration  assignments  must  be 
   defined accurately in order for TMCS properly report network conditions.  
   This is  done thru TMCS's Network Configuration Management command.  The 
   data managed by these commands can be divided into 5 groups:

       1.  Cluster Data
       2.  Host Location Data
       3.  Host Names Data
       4.  Node Names Data
       5.  XOM Host Data


   COMMON MISTAKES / PROBLEMS 

   .  TMCS will not recognize a node that has not been named, therefore that 
   node will not be reported.

   .  The TMCS display will report hosts missing if a host is assigned to a
   node that does not exist or if the host location is assigned to the wrong
   node or if the node has not been named.

   In  order  to  see  the node name and host location in the  TMCS  DISPLAY 
   command the following commands must be performed:

     SET NODE NAME
       syntax:   SET NODEs NAME nnnn name
       function: assign a name to node nnnn, as a means of tracking that
                 node more easily

     SET HOST LOCATION
       syntax:   SET HOST LOCATION {host#} {node#} [position]
       function: assign host locations used in the host missing list


   CONFIGURATION PARAMETER DEFINITIONS
   -----------------------------------

   Three parameter groups: 

        1.  NETWORK
        2.  TMCS
        3.  NEM

   NETWORK PARAMETERS ( .A FILE )

     Specify charateristics of the network to be monitored and MUST be
     properly defined for TMCS/NEM to operate properly and efficiently.
     They  play  a major  part  in determining the disk and core usage 
     requirements.

   TMCS PARAMETERS ( .A FILE )
  
     Defines the Concurrent Pascal Preprocessor configuration flags and
     parameters specific to TMCS.
         
     COMMON PITFALLS AND MISTAKES
                
       1.  Misspelling of  $ENABLE  or the  switch name  will produce 
           errors in CPPRO (v10.00 on)
               
       2.  Rule of thumb for most parameter text strings:
    
           String MUST end with a backslash "\" and have an EVEN number
           characters INCLUDING the "\"
              
       3.  Node_Mask and Host_Mask MUST be a POWER OF 2
           (ie. 2, 4, 8, 16, 32, 64, 128, 256, 512, 1024, 2048, 4096, ...)
          
       4.  Node_Hash_Max & Host_Hash_Max  MUST be specified as a PRIME #
 
              
   NEM PARAMETERS ( .A FILE )

     Defines the configuration parameters that relate specifically to NEM
     and are necessary in determining disk and core usage.  They MUST be
     defined in the .A file for NEM.
      
     COMMON PITFALLS AND MISTAKES
           
       1.  The sup login string (ERLOG_TEXT) may have a max of 24 character
           between '  '

           NOTE:  the (:4:) counts as only one character

       2.  The Consumer_Max MUST be set to:

               1 > USER_MAX set for TMCS  
            or 2 > USER_MAX set for TMCS  with RELOAD ENABLEDD


   TYMFILE PARAMETERS (.T FILE)
   ----------------------------

     Configuration parameters from both ISIS and the PASCAL program are
     defined for the PASCAL Nucleus via the slot .T file.



   COMMAND FILE REMINDERS
   ----------------------

   TMCS
 
     1.  Check for Version # changes *** DON'T FORGET PNUC VERSION # ***
         
     2.  V10.00 and > MUST contain Concurrent Pascal Preprocessor
         
     3.  Important when upgrading versions of TMCS: verify patch file
         references are correct for new version.  Assembling in old  
         patches can cause numerous problems.
             
   TMDM
     
     1.  PCOM will hang because the COPY command line is too long.
         To get around this you can:

           1.  split COPY into two COPY command lines,  OR
           2.  run (UPL)COM instead 


   ESTIMATING RESOURCE REQUIREMENTS
   --------------------------------

     TMRE v1.01 (for TMCS v7.05/7.08) output:
    
       1.  TOTAL NUMBER OF CYLINDERS needed by TMCS slot

           ****  Value from TMRE is decimal and MUST be  ****
           ****  converted to HEX for use in DSC file.   ****

       2.  Max number of nodes in a btree file -  btree_max parameter
       3.  MINIMUM MEMORY required for TMCS slot

           ****  ADD  10%  to memory estimate  ****

     TMRE v2.00 (for TMCS v10.00) output:
  
       1-2  Same output as v1.01 EXCEPT:

       3.  TMRE no longer gives estimates MINIMUM MEMORY requirements.  A
           formula will be available with the release documents to determine
           memory usage.


  
  
   GENERATION REQUIREMENTS

   This category describes additional actions need for TMCS and NEM
   to function.

   VALIDATION
   ----------
   In order to login properly for TMCS and NEM after instalation, the
   following network usernames need to be validated with host numbers.

   NETALARM
     ALARM facility enable
     no pasword required
     origin host:  TMCS host
     home host: external alarm system host
     function:  username TMCS Alarm facility uses to log into the external 
                alarm system host
  
   NETELF
     RELOAD facility enable
     no password required
     login over shut
     origin host:  TMCS host
     home host: destination ELF host
     function:  username TMCS Reload facility uses to log into ELF to begin
                the node or slot reload process

   NETEVENT
     no login over shut
     no password required
     origin host: TMCS host
     home host: NEM host
     function:  username TMCS uses to log into NEM to access log data

   ENTEVOP
     no login over shut
     home host: NEM host
     function:  username used by NEM operations personnel to log into NEM
   
   NETNTCN
     RELOAD facility enable
     no login over shut
     no password required
     origin host:  TMCS host
     home host: Network Console host
     function:  username TMCS Reload facility uses to log into Network Console
                to begin the XOM configuration parameter restoration process

   OMNC
     RELOAD facility enable
     colon option required
     password:  NETWORK CONSOLE
     group:     0
     origin host:  Network Console host
     home host: all X.25/X.75 XOM hosts
     function:  username Network Console uses to log into an operations
                monitor XOM.

   TMCS
     no password required
     home host: TMCS host
     function:  username that TMCS users log into


   NETWORK CONSOLE Username
     RELOAD facility enable
     function:  username that TMCS uses for the secondary Network Console
                login, validated by TMCS master user in TMCS slot


    PROBE Username
     function:  username that TMCS uses to log into Probe, username and
                password is maintained by SET PROBE PASSWORD cmmand in TMCS



   GUIDLINES FOR SYSTEM UPGRADES
   -----------------------------

     Upgrading the network monitoring tools is done according to the system
     are that is changing (i.e.; source code, disk file structure, TYM file,
     etc.).  



   I.  Upgrading TMCS from Version 7.5 or 7.8 to Version 10.0 or 10.01
       ===============================================================

     Procedure:

       1.  Archive the data base
       2.  Gen and load TMDM Version 1.03 and enter "RECONFIGURE" to
           reconfigure the data base to be compatible with TMCS Version 10.0
           or 10.01
       3.  Gen and load TMCS Version 10.0 or 10.01

     Notes:

       o  If TMDM is interrupted while in the process of reconfiguring,
          the data base will most likely be destroyed; hence the importance 
          archiving the original data base.
   
      o  Because of a memory space limitation in the TMDM Version 1.03 code, 
         it is not possible to reconfigure a data base with this version of 
         TMDM once it has been configured to be compatible with Version 10.0 
         or 10.01

   II  Upgrading TMCS from Version 10.0 or 10.01 to Version 10.10
       ==========================================================

       1.  Archive the data base
       2.  Gen and load TMDM Version 2.0 and enter "RECONFIGURE" to
           reconfigure the data base to be compatible with TMCS Version 10.10
       3.  Gen and load TMCS Version 10.10

   III Upgrading TMCS from Version 7.5 or 7.8 to Version 10.10
       =======================================================
       1.  Archive the data base
       2.  Gen and load TMDM Version 1.03 and enter "RECONFIGURE" to
           reconfigure the data base to be compatible with TMCS Version 10.0
           or 10.01
       3.  Gen and load TMDM Version 2.0 and enter "RECONFIGURE" to
           reconfigure the data base to be compatible with TMCS Version 10.10
       4.  Gen and load TMCS Version 10.10
   


   TMCS COLOR TERMINAL CONTROL SEQUENCES

   As you are probably aware TMCS is capable of emulating different types
   of terminal/monitors.  Those currently supported are:
   
              BLACK/WHITE          COLOR
               o  ADM1              o  ISC2400
               o  ADM3              o  ISC8900
               o  HP2621
               o  SCANSET
               o  DEC VT100

   The following is a description of the control sequences used by the
   ISC2400 & ISC8900 color terminal.  This includes the special sequences
   for color LOG and DISPLAY output.
    

   The cursor function is listed with the decimal value equivalent.  The
   decimal value requires an ASCII character set equivalent.  The symbols
   are as follows:
   
         +     Specifies to concantenate the characters together, unless
               bounded by parentheses or angle brackets.  If  bounded by
               parenthesis or angle brackets add the numeric values.

         =     Specifies the literal equal sign.
       
        ( )    Specifies the  value  of  the  expression  is  a  single
               numeric character and should be translated as such.  For 
               example, if the value of the  expression  is  (14+1), it
               is translated into the ASCII equivalent of 15.

        < >    Specifies each numeric character needs to be translated. 
               For  example,  if  the  expression  is  <14+1>,  it  is 
               translated   into   the   ASCII   equivalent  of  the 
               characters 1 and 5.
   










      ISC2400 - INTELLIGENT SYSTEMS CORP. COLOR TERMINAL

    Charaters                                    Function
    -----------------------------------          ------------------------
    27 + [ + 1 + A                               Cursor up
    27 + [ + 1 + B                               Cursor down
    27 + [ + 1 + C                               Cursor right
    27 + [ + 1 + D                               Cursor left

    27 + [ + H                                   Home cursor 
                                                 - upper left corner -

    27 + [ + <row#+1> + ; + <column#+1> + H      Position cursor is
                                                 on screen

    27 + [ + H + 27 + [ + J                      Clear from cursor to end
                                                 of screen

    SPECIAL SEQUENCES FOR LOG & DISPLAY OUTPUT:
    
    27 + [ + ? + 2 + h + 27 + [ + ? + 6 + 1      Put terminal in ANSI mode
    (l = lowercase L)                            & set origin mode to upper
                                                 left corner (home=1:1)
    GRAPIC SEQUENCES:

    27 + [ + (color#) + m                        Print color
    27 + [ + 5 + m                               Set flashing
    27 + [ + m                                   End color
    27 + [+ 2 + 4 + ; + 8 + 0 + H                Exit display










      ISC8900 - INTELLIGENT SYSTEMS CORP. COLOR TERMINAL

    Charaters                                    Function
    -----------------------------------          ----------------------
    28                                           Cursor up
    10                                           Cursor down
    25                                           Cursor right
    26                                           Cursor left
    8                                            Home cursor 
                                                 - upper left corner -

    3 + <column#> + (2*row#)                     Position cursor is
                                                  on screen
    12                                           Clear from cursor to
                                                  end of screen

    SPECIAL SEQUENCES FOR LOG & DISPLAY OUTPUT:
    
    14                                           Set terminal to print
                                                  double size characters
    15                                           Reset character height
                                                  to normal
    7                                            Set color to white
    6 + (color# + 64)                            Set color & set flashing
    6 + (color#)                                 Set color but not flashing
    3 + 79 + 46                                  Exit display



