    TIPS ON MENU SERVICE - FOR PRIVATE NETWORK PROJECT MANAGEMENT TRAINING 
    ----------------------------------------------------------------------
    ----------------------------------------------------------------------


Written by : Fun-Lin Chen, HQ Technical Svc, Application's Support Dept.
      Date : Jan 06, 1986




   I. What is Menu Service ?

       A Tymnet software product that provides a very friendly menu screen,
       allows users easy access to a variety of hosts and network services.

       The key words are : friendly menu screen
                           easy access
                           variety of hosts and network services.

   II. The Advantages of Using Menu Service

       - Friendly Menu Screen
         It is 100% configurable. Customers have choices of having broadcast
         messages or not, one menu or multiple menus, what to display on 
         screen, what to use for selection fields.

       - Easy Access
         One login sequence versus multiple login sequences, eliminate keying
         errors.

       - Variety of Hosts and Network Services
         This includes Tymnet or outside information vendors. Customers can
         store all kinds of services in one place.

       - Other Good Features
         * Multiple Logical Slots (16 per physical slot)
           Allows customers to set up multiple levels of user accessing.
         * Inactivity Timer
           Saves connect charges if service is not in use.
         * AutoLogin/AutoLogoff
           Special application when customers choose not to have screen 
           displays.
         * Password Option
           Depends on the application, customers can choose to have users key
           in passwords or to have passwords kept in the Sysgen file (of cause
           we can use Cipher to achieve the security protection).
         * Project Code Collecting
           Very good feature for costs/expenses distributing.


   III. Things to Watch Out For

       - Password Option
         This is not for keeping unauthorized users out from accessing to the
         Menu slot. This is to give the customers the flexibility of what to
         do with the passwords.

       - No Way Out
         This is the most critical issue. Users do not have a good way to
         interrupt circuit building, cases like incorrect selections or
         unsuccessful logins. The only way to get out of the waiting would
         be "put the terminal offline".
         Bug report has been sent to NTD. So far, it's not resolved yet.

       - Screen Echo Problem
         Put CMT and Menu Service together, sometimes it will cause some 
         characters not being displayed. HQTECH is working together with NTD
         on this problem. At this stage, we don't know the cause of the 
         problem yet.
   
       - Sup Timeout When Using Manual Login Problem
         Manual Login is one of the nice features in Menu Service. But
         if the user does not send in login sequence in time, the Sup timeout
         sometimes will cause slot to be halted. This is a known problem
         to NTD and us.

   IV. Marketing Information
   
       Menu Service is in Limited Release phase right now. So far, we have
       6 customers in PublicNet. There are several PrivateNet customers
       show great interests in it as we were told. But they would probably
       prefer to make the decision when it's in full release. The general 
       concern from the sales is we don't have a External Reference Spec. 
       Marketing is working on this issue.



